    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade FD3S RX-7, a masterpiece of 1990s lightweight engineering. This specimen features the 13B-REW twin-rotor engine, utilizing its factory sequential twin-turbocharger configuration for a seamless power band. The chassis maintains its perfect 50/50 weight distribution and sophisticated four-wheel double-wishbone suspension, ensuring surgical precision through corners. The drivetrain is anchored by a robust five-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential, both functioning with factory-new tactility. Meticulously maintained with a pristine vacuum system and original apex seals showing excellent compression, this R1-spec example is free of any mechanical or aesthetic blemishes. A true time-capsule for the serious collector.",
